<subSubSection box="[199,1299,1808,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,692,1943]" box="[199,1299,1808,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1808,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang, He &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" box="[565,668,1809,1834]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Bethylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexus">
<emphasis box="[565,668,1809,1834]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">convexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the distinctly protuberant eyes of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="363" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,692,1943]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1844,1870]" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of this genus by having head distinctly longer than wide, median clypeal lobe distinctly protuberant with apex rounded, eyes distinctly protuberant (
<figureCitation box="[1292,1373,1880,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1908]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Bethylus convexus sp. nov. holotype, ♀. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Mandible; d. Antenna; e. Head, lateral view; f. Mesosoma, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Forewing. Scale bars: 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775730/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
), and metapostnotum with median polished ridge (
<figureCitation box="[652,729,1916,1943]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1908]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Bethylus convexus sp. nov. holotype, ♀. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Mandible; d. Antenna; e. Head, lateral view; f. Mesosoma, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Forewing. Scale bars: 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775730/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="363">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
